    "title": "Ludo",
    "content": "# Ludo\n\n**From Latin** — *ludo*, first-person singular present active indicative of *ludere*: **\"I play\"**, **\"I sport\"**, **\"I am playing\"**.\n\nThe root *ludere* extends to: *ludus* (game, sport, play) and *ludicrus* (playful, sportive) — from which English gets **ludicrous** (originally: \"pertaining to play,\" later: \"absurd\").\n\n## In the Vault\n\n\"Ludo\" is the core metaphor behind [[Notes/Futur Ludoism|Futur Ludoism]] — life as an infinite game. The philosophy casts existence as a game we play, where the goal is to play at a higher level (the meta-game), rather than to win or finish.\n\nThe prefix signals that existence is:\n- **Active** — we are players, not spectators\n- **Processual** — the playing itself is what matters\n- **Structured** — games have rules ([[Substrate of Action]], principles, causality)\n- **Masterable** — like any game, existence can be understood and played better\n\n## Related\n\n- [[Notes/Futur Ludoism|Futur Ludoism]] — the philosophy built on this metaphor\n- [[Archive/MetaLudo-Existentialism|MetaLudo-Existentialism]] — predecessor framework\n\n#moc/philosophy",
