    "id": "the-beginnings-of-ludaria",
    "title": "The Beginnings of Ludaria",
    "content": "# The Beginnings of Ludaria\n\nI have thought of writing a book for quite some time now. Fictional of course. And I had just come up with the idea for my writings, that actually sounds good.\n\n## The Magic\n\nI will take a very basic approach to magic. The reality of this world is like ours, but they have a very special force I will call The Path. Essentially it is based on my philosophy Ludoism. Namely that everything is made of actions, they are what move us between frames. There is nothing between frames, there is just a process. And this processes are what make everything possible, essentially semi infinite and complex patterns in base reality. Everything is the result of those actions. And The Path, is what refers to the Action Set, a set of actions that make something something. For example a rock, is just a set of actions together in a specific repeating pattern. Everything is just actions, so what if conscious beings have a soul, and the defining property of the soul is to allow us to perceive and alter the action pattern that makes anything. That is **The Path.**\n\nTo give an example of what magic in that world is capable, by altering the actions, we can think of them as an array in the nothingness, that repeats itself, a fractal maybe. Let's say we have a flame, a flame in itself is just a burning of a material that gives some frequency, but in itself anything burns because it can work as a fuel. *By being able to change the rules by which fire operates we can essentially burn everything or turn anything into anything, for example changing the rules of atomic structures we can turn gold to dirt and vice versa.*\n\nThough as reality is a complex set of actions, it folds back on itself in a pattern, it self regenerates. The larger the change the more reality acts against it. Which is why powerful spells are hard to make and rare. Because while small spells change the rules a little\n\n## The World\n\nAs magic has been **everpresent** in this Semi-Medieval Fantasy world, it has naturally developed differently to ours. For example, as there are no limits on what can be changed to what(though complex shapes like humans are almost impossible to make from dirt), the food is abundant, as we can just change the rules or speed of growth of cattle and wheat... As such, while there is a farming class, it is honestly quite small. Made of few mid size farms. As there is no need for large farms.\n\nBecause magic has always been present, and is the defining quality of the power in the world, it is essentially what decides someone's social status. Powerful families or clans have developed which hold their spells, complex spells. For example there are families specializing in fire for example. And not just the fire we see it but all that can burn, they can burn the reality itself in most extreme cases.\n\n## The Twist\n\nMain character has unique ability to act between moments. The way this is explain is through my philosophy Ludoism. Where the world operates in actions, or moves as it was first concieved.",
