    "content": "# Obsidian Plugins That Quietly Transformed a PhD Workflow\r\n\r\n> **Medium member-only story** — the full content is behind Medium's paywall and was not directly accessible. What follows is based on the public preview and the article's framing.\r\n\r\n## About the Article\r\n\r\nWritten by Len, a Ph.D. student in data science / Python, published Nov 17, 2025. The author describes this as a personal tour of Obsidian plugins that \"quietly transformed\" how they read, write, code, and manage the chaos of a PhD.\r\n\r\nThe author's framing: not a flashy \"Top 10\" list, but tools that solved small daily frictions in sustainable ways.\r\n\r\n**Source:** [medium.com/@lennart.dde](https://medium.com/@lennart.dde/obsidian-plugins-that-quietly-transformed-my-phd-workflow-3d1478446360)\r\n\r\n## Known Context (from the preview)\r\n\r\nThe author's PhD workflow revolves around:\r\n- **Reading** — research papers, academic sources\r\n- **Writing** — papers, thesis, notes\r\n- **Coding** — data science / Python work\r\n- **Managing chaos** — the organizational overhead of a PhD\r\n\r\nThe articles promises plugins across these four areas.\r\n\r\n## Related\r\n\r\n- [[Resources/Obsidian Getting Started - MOCs and Tags]]\r\n- [[MOCs/School]]\n\n#resource #moc/organization",
