    "id": "cross-folder-project-search-in-obsidian",
    "title": "Cross-Folder Project Search in Obsidian",
    "content": "# Cross-Folder Project Search in Obsidian\r\n\r\n**Context:** Projects are now each a subfolder in `Projects/`. The file explorer shows folders, not files — you lose at-a-glance overview and cross-project search is clunky. How to fix this with Bases (core plugin) and a few conventions.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## Approach 1: Bases Projects Dashboard (primary)\r\n\r\nBases is Obsidian's core plugin — no install needed. It renders interactive tables, cards, or lists from frontmatter properties. Create a `.base` file at `Projects/_Projects.base` to get a sortable, filterable project overview.\r\n\r\n### What a Projects base looks like\r\n\r\n```yaml\r\nquery:\r\n  folder: \"Projects\"\r\n  depth: 2\r\n  limit: 50\r\ncolumns:\r\n  - key: file.name\r\n    label: \"Project\"\r\n    type: text\r\n  - key: status\r\n    label: \"Status\"\r\n    type: text\r\n  - key: created\r\n    label: \"Created\"\r\n    type: date\r\n  - key: tags\r\n    label: \"Tags\"\r\n    type: tags\r\n  - key: file.link\r\n    label: \"Open\"\r\n    type: link\r\nview: table\r\nsortBy: status\r\nsortAsc: true\r\n```\r\n\r\n### View modes\r\n\r\n| Mode | Best for |\r\n|------|----------|\r\n| **Table** | Columns of frontmatter data — sortable, filterable |\r\n| **Cards** | Visual overview with selected fields as card headers |\r\n| **List** | Simple list with one or two fields visible |\r\n\r\n### Interactive benefits\r\n\r\n- **Click-to-filter** — click a status cell and see only \"planning\" projects\r\n- **Inline editing** — change a frontmatter field directly from the base view\r\n- **Drag-to-reorder** — rearrange rows manually\r\n- **No query language** — point-and-click configuration\r\n\r\n### Embedded Bases in MOCs\r\n\r\nEvery MOC note already uses embedded Bases blocks for its \"All X Notes\" auto-list. Pattern:\r\n\r\n```base\r\nquery:\r\n  tags: [\"#MOC/<area>\"]\r\n  excludeTags: [\"#moc\"]\r\nview: list\r\nsortBy: file.name\r\nsortAsc: true\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\ncreated: 2026-05-21\r\nupdated: 2026-05-21\r\ntype: research\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Approach 3: Tag-Based Aggregation (complementary)\r\n\r\nNot standalone but a force multiplier. A dedicated tag pattern makes all project content queryable in Bases or search.\r\n\r\n### Proposed tags\r\n\r\n```\r\n#hermes/project          → every project root file\r\n#hermes/project/active   → active projects\r\n#hermes/project/planning → planning phase\r\n#hermes/project/archive  → completed/archived\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Effect on Bases\r\n\r\nFilter a Projects base by `tags` column — click `#hermes/project` to see only project files.\r\n\r\n### Effect on search\r\n\r\nType `#hermes/project` in any search bar to scope results.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\ncreated: 2026-05-21\r\nupdated: 2026-05-21\r\ntype: research\r\n---\r\n\r\n## Comparison Matrix\r\n\r\n| Approach | Install needed | Interactive | Effort | Best for |\r\n|----------|:---:|:---:|:---:|----------|\r\n| Bases .base file | No (core) | Yes | Medium | Primary project dashboard |\r\n| MOC embedded Bases | No (core) | Partially | Low | Tag-filtered auto-lists in MOCs |\r\n| Omnisearch plugin | Yes (community) | Yes | Low | Daily fuzzy search across all content |\r\n| Tag aggregation | No | No | Low | Complement to any other approach |\r\n| Dashboard _INDEX.md | No | Partially | Medium | Combined views in one place |\r\n\r\n**Recommended stack:**\r\n1. **Projects `.base` file** as the primary interactive overview\r\n2. **MOC embedded Bases blocks** for all MOC auto-lists\r\n3. **Tag pattern** (`#hermes/project`) to unify querying\r\n4. **Omnisearch** if you want the best raw search experience\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\ncreated: 2026-05-21\r\nupdated: 2026-05-21\r\ntype: research\r\n---\r\n\r\n#moc/organization\r\n\r\n## Related\r\n\r\n- [[Projects/_INDEX|Projects Index]]\r\n- [[_README|Vault Convention]] — see the Project Structure Convention section",
